{"title_page": "2005 Western Kentucky Hilltoppers football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| mode = football\n| year = 2005\n| team= Western Kentucky Hilltoppers\n| image = WKU Hilltoppers wordmark.png\n| image_size= 175\n| conference= Gateway Football Conference\n| division= \n| short_conf= Gateway\n| STATSRank = \n| FCSCoachRank = \n| record = 6\u20135\n| conf_record = 4\u20133\n| head_coach= [[David Elson]]\n| hc_year =3rd\n| off_coach= \n| oc_year = \n| def_coach= \n| dc_year = \n| off_scheme= \n| def_scheme=\n| stadium= [[Houchens Industries\u2013L. T. Smith Stadium]]\n| champion = \n| bowl = \n| bowl_result = \n}}\n{{2005 Gateway Football Conference standings}}\nThe '''2005 Western Kentucky Hilltoppers football team''' represented [[Western Kentucky Hilltoppers football|Western Kentucky University]] in the [[2005 NCAA Division I-AA football season]] and were coached by [[David Elson]].  The Hilltoppers started the season strong, but after being ranked number 1 in Division 1-AA, they lost their last four games and failed to make the playoffs for the first time since 1999.<ref>[https://www.bgdailynews.com/sports/2005-a-year-in-review---tragedies-near-misses/article_ef91b9b2-cd4c-54ad-b544-33a7943ff2bb.html 2005: A Year in Review - Tragedies, near misses By NORM HANEY, The Daily News, Jan 1, 2006  retrieved 4 April 2020.]</ref>\n\nThe team included future [[National Football League|NFL]] players [[Curtis Hamilton (American football)|Curtis Hamilton]] and Greg Ryan.    Erik Losey and Antonio Thomas were named to the AP All American team and Chris James made the 1AA All-Star Team.  The All-Conference team included Losey, Thomas, James, Lerron Moore, Marion Rumph, Deion Holts, Dennis Mitchell, and Daniel Williams.<ref>[https://wkusports.com/documents/2019/7/17/2019_WKU_Football_Media_Guide.pdf WKU Football Media Guide retrieved 31 March 2020.]</ref>\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| rankyear = 