4/moscow-schools-start-rolling-out-flexible-attendance-and-remote-learning-policies-to-fight-coronavirus-spread|title=Moscow schools start rolling out 'flexible attendance' and remote learning policies to fight coronavirus spread|last=|first=|date=March 14, 2020|website=meduza.io|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> The following day private schools in [[Moscow]] were urged to suspend operations for two weeks while several schools located within foreign embassies in Moscow were advised to enter a two-week quarantine.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rbc.ru/society/14/03/2020/5e6bf6d99a7947dd214719e7|title=\u0414\u0435\u0441\u044f\u0442\u0438 \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u043c \u043f\u0440\u0438 \u043f\u043e\u0441\u043e\u043b\u044c\u0441\u0442\u0432\u0430\u0445 \u0432 \u041c\u043e\u0441\u043a\u0432\u0435 \u0440\u0435\u043a\u043e\u043c\u0435\u043d\u0434\u043e\u0432\u0430\u043b\u0438 \u0443\u0439\u0442\u0438 \u043d\u0430 \u043a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d|last=|first=|date=14 March 2020|website=\u0420\u0411\u041a|language=ru|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref><ref name=\":19\" /> Moscow's chief sanitary doctor signed a decree banning visitors to boarding schools and orphanages.<ref name=\":20\">{{cite web|url=https://www.themoscowtimes.com/2020/03/16/coronavirus-in-russia-the-latest-news-march-16-a69117|title=Coronavirus in Russia: The Latest News|last=Times|first=The Moscow|date=2020-03-16|website=The Moscow Times|language=en|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> On 16 March, Moscow extended measures to closing public schools, universities, athletic schools and supplemental education institutions from 21 March to 12 April.<ref name=\":20\" /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://meduza.io/en/news/2020/03/16/moscow-extends-coronavirus-measures-to-ban-outdoor-events-close-schools-and-isolate-all-u-s-and-european-arrivals|title=Moscow extends coronavirus measures to ban outdoor events, close schools, and isolate all U.S. and European arrivals|last=|first=|date=March 16, 2020|website=meduza.io|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> Quarantine in all Russian schools since March 23. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.1tv.ru/news/2020-03-18/382190-karantin_vo_vseh_rossiyskih_shkolah_nachinaetsya_s_23_marta|title=\u041a\u0430\u0440\u0430\u043d\u0442\u0438\u043d \u0432\u043e \u0432\u0441\u0435\u0445 \u0440\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0439\u0441\u043a\u0438\u0445 \u0448\u043a\u043e\u043b\u0430\u0445 \u043d\u0430\u0447\u0438\u043d\u0430\u0435\u0442\u0441\u044f \u0441 23 \u043c\u0430\u0440\u0442\u0430. \u041d\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0441\u0442\u0438. \u041f\u0435\u0440\u0432\u044b\u0439 \u043a\u0430\u043d\u0430\u043b|accessdate=Mar 26, 2020|via=www.1tv.ru}}</ref>\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Russia]]\n|\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; border-right:none;\" |{{flagdeco|Rwanda}}|| style=\"text-align:left; border-left:none;\" | Rwanda || 3,388,696 || 75,713\n|\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Rwanda]]\n|<ref name=\"UNESCO\" />\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; border-right:none;\" |{{flagdeco|Saint Lucia}}|| style=\"text-align:left; border-left:none;\" | Saint Lucia || 30,925 || 2,237\n|\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saint Lucia]]\n|<ref name=\"UNESCO\" />\n|- \n| style=\"text-align:left; border-right:none;\" |{{flagdeco|Saudi Arabia}}|| style=\"text-align:left; border-left:none;\" | Saudi Arabia || 6,789,773 || 1,620,491\n|\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Saudi Arabia]]\n|<ref name=\"UNESCO\" />\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; border-right:none;\" |{{flagdeco|Senegal}}|| style=\"text-align:left; border-left:none;\" | Senegal || 3,475,647 || 184,879\n|\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Senegal]]\n|<ref name=\"UNESCO\" />\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; border-right:none;\" |{{flagdeco|Serbia}}|| style=\"text-align:left; border-left:none;\" | Serbia || 964,796 || 256,172\n|Schools are closed.<ref name=\":15\" />\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in S