 the Witwatersrand|Wits University]] in [[Johannesburg]] who tested positive for coronavirus.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/africa/south-africa-orders-schools-closed-as-covid-19-spreads/1767271|title=South Africa orders schools closed as COVID-19 spreads|website=aa.com.tr|access-date=2020-03-16}}</ref>\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in South Africa]]||<ref name=\"UNESCO\" />\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; border-right:none;\" |{{flagdeco|Spain}}|| style=\"text-align:left; border-left:none;\" | Spain || 7,696,101 || 2,010,183\n|Schools are closed.<ref name=\":15\" />\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Spain]]\n|<ref name=\"UNESCO\" />\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; border-right:none;\" |{{flagdeco|Sri Lanka}}|| style=\"text-align:left; border-left:none;\" | Sri Lanka || 4,917,578 || 300,794\n|The government ordered to close schools from 12 March to 20 April which also marks the end of the first term.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://colombogazette.com/2020/03/12/government-schools-to-be-closed-till-april/|title=Government schools to be closed till April|website=colombogazette.com|date=12 March 2020|accessdate=18 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://economynext.com/sri-lanka-shuts-schools-over-virus-rumours-57622,%20https://economynext.com/sri-lanka-shuts-schools-over-virus-rumours-57622/|title=Sri Lanka shuts schools over virus rumours|date=2020-03-12|website=EconomyNext|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref> The [[Private tutoring in Asia|private tuition classes and tutorials]] are also closed for two weeks until 26 March.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newsfirst.lk/2020/03/12/schools-closed-till-april-20th-no-tution-classes-till-march-26th/|title=Schools closed till April 20th , No tution classes till March 26th|date=2020-03-12|website=Sri Lanka News - Newsfirst|language=en|access-date=18 March 2020}}</ref>\n|[[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Sri Lanka]]\n|<ref name=\"UNESCO\" />\n|-\n| style=\"text-align:left; border-right:none;\" |{{flagdeco|Sudan}}|| sty